msgctxt "an6.54:6.1"
msgid "Atha kho jātibhūmakānaṃ upāsakānaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then the local lay followers thought to themselves:"

msgctxt "an6.54:6.2"
msgid ""
"“mayaṃ kho bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paccupaṭṭhitā "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.54:6.3"
msgid ""
"Atha ca pana āgantukā bhikkhū pakkamanti, na saṇṭhanti, riñcanti āvāsaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.54:6.4"
msgid ""
"Ko nu kho hetu ko paccayo yena āgantukā bhikkhū pakkamanti, na saṇṭhanti, "
"riñcanti āvāsan”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.54:6.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho jātibhūmakānaṃ upāsakānaṃ etadahosi: “ayaṃ kho āyasmā dhammiko "
"āgantuke bhikkhū akkosati … pe …."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.54:6.6"
msgid ""
"Yannūna mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ dhammikaṃ pabbājeyyāma sabbaso jātibhūmiyaṃ sattahi "
"āvāsehī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Why don’t we banish Venerable Dhammika from all seven monasteries in our "
"native land?”"

msgctxt "an6.54:6.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho jātibhūmakā upāsakā yenāyasmā dhammiko tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; "
"upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ dhammikaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then the local lay followers went up to Venerable Dhammika and said to him:"

msgctxt "an6.54:6.8"
msgid ""
"“pakkamatu, bhante, āyasmā dhammiko sabbaso jātibhūmiyaṃ sattahi āvāsehī”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, please leave all seven monasteries in our native land.”"

msgctxt "an6.54:6.9"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato dhammikassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Dhammika thought:"

msgctxt "an6.54:6.10"
msgid ""
"“pabbājito khomhi jātibhūmakehi upāsakehi sabbaso jātibhūmiyaṃ sattahi "
"āvāsehi."
msgstr ""
"“I’ve been banished by the local lay followers from all seven monasteries in "
"my native land."

msgctxt "an6.54:6.11"
msgid "Kahaṃ nu kho dāni gacchāmī”ti?"
msgstr "Where am I to go now?”"

msgctxt "an6.54:6.12"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato dhammikassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Dhammika thought:"

msgctxt "an6.54:6.13"
msgid "“yannūnāhaṃ yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti."
msgstr "“Why don’t I go to see the Buddha?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā dhammiko pattacīvaramādāya yena rājagahaṃ tena pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Dhammika took his bowl and robe and set out for Rājagaha."

msgctxt "an6.54:7.2"
msgid ""
"Anupubbena yena rājagahaṃ gijjhakūṭo pabbato yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ "
"kho āyasmantaṃ dhammikaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Eventually he came to Rājagaha and the Vulture’s Peak. He went up to the "
"Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "an6.54:7.3"
msgid "“handa kuto nu tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa dhammika, āgacchasī”ti?"
msgstr "“So, Brahmin Dhammika, where have you come from?”"

msgctxt "an6.54:7.4"
msgid ""
"“Pabbājito ahaṃ, bhante, jātibhūmakehi upāsakehi sabbaso jātibhūmiyaṃ "
"sattahi āvāsehī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, I’ve been banished by the local lay followers from all seven "
"monasteries in my native land.”"

msgctxt "an6.54:7.5"
msgid ""
"“Alaṃ, brāhmaṇa dhammika, kiṃ te iminā, yaṃ taṃ tato tato pabbājenti, so "
"tvaṃ tato tato pabbājito mameva santike āgacchasi."
msgstr ""
"“Enough, Brahmin Dhammika, what’s that to you? Now that you’ve been banished "
"from all of those places, you have come to me."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:8.1"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, brāhmaṇa dhammika, sāmuddikā vāṇijā tīradassiṃ sakuṇaṃ gahetvā "
"nāvāya samuddaṃ ajjhogāhanti."
msgstr ""
"Once upon a time, some sea-merchants set sail for the ocean deeps, taking "
"with them a land-spotting bird."

#. VAR: atīradakkhiṇiyā → atīradassaniyā (s1-3) | atīradassiyā (mr)
msgctxt "an6.54:8.2"
msgid "Te atīradakkhiṇiyā nāvāya tīradassiṃ sakuṇaṃ muñcanti."
msgstr "When their ship was out of sight of land, they released the bird."

msgctxt "an6.54:8.3"
msgid ""
"So gacchateva puratthimaṃ disaṃ, gacchati pacchimaṃ disaṃ, gacchati uttaraṃ "
"disaṃ, gacchati dakkhiṇaṃ disaṃ, gacchati uddhaṃ, gacchati anudisaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It flew right away to the east, the west, the north, the south, upwards, and "
"in-between."

#. VAR: tathāgatakova → tathāgato (mr)
msgctxt "an6.54:8.4"
msgid "Sace so samantā tīraṃ passati, tathāgatakova hoti."
msgstr "If it saw land on any side, it went there and stayed."

msgctxt "an6.54:8.5"
msgid "Sace pana so samantā tīraṃ na passati tameva nāvaṃ paccāgacchati."
msgstr "But if it saw no land on any side it returned to the ship."

msgctxt "an6.54:8.6"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa dhammika, yaṃ taṃ tato tato pabbājenti so tvaṃ tato "
"tato pabbājito mameva santike āgacchasi."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, now that you’ve been banished from all of those places, you "
"have come to me."

# Here khandha refers to the secondary trunks rather than branches. BB uses “branch “and” section” for khandha, then “branch” again for sakha.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.369"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:9.1"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, brāhmaṇa dhammika, rañño korabyassa suppatiṭṭho nāma "
"nigrodharājā ahosi pañcasākho sītacchāyo manoramo."
msgstr ""
"Once upon a time, King Koravya had a royal banyan tree with five trunks "
"called ‘Well Planted’. It was shady and lovely."

# The size is only moderately hyperbolic: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thimmamma_Marrimanu
msgctxt "an6.54:9.2"
msgid ""
"Suppatiṭṭhassa kho pana, brāhmaṇa dhammika, nigrodharājassa dvādasayojanāni "
"abhiniveso ahosi, pañca yojanāni mūlasantānakānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Its canopy spread over twelve leagues, while the network of roots spread for "
"five leagues."

msgctxt "an6.54:9.3"
msgid ""
"Suppatiṭṭhassa kho pana, brāhmaṇa dhammika, nigrodharājassa tāva mahantāni "
"phalāni ahesuṃ;"
msgstr "Its fruits were as large as"

msgctxt "an6.54:9.4"
msgid "seyyathāpi nāma āḷhakathālikā."
msgstr "a rice pot."

msgctxt "an6.54:9.5"
msgid "Evamassa sādūni phalāni ahesuṃ;"
msgstr "And they were as sweet as"

msgctxt "an6.54:9.6"
msgid "seyyathāpi nāma khuddaṃ madhuṃ anelakaṃ."
msgstr "pure wild honey."

# This story, a very rare specimen of extended narrative in the suttas, has the ring of a very old tale. Not only because of the folk beliefs it depends on, but the conceit of an entire kingdom living in one tree, no matter how large, sounds like a tribal society.
#. VAR: khandhaṃ migā → migapakkhino (bj, s1-3) | migapakkhiyo (pts1)
msgctxt "an6.54:9.7"
msgid ""
"Suppatiṭṭhassa kho pana, brāhmaṇa dhammika, nigrodharājassa ekaṃ khandhaṃ "
"rājā paribhuñjati saddhiṃ itthāgārena, ekaṃ khandhaṃ balakāyo paribhuñjati, "
"ekaṃ khandhaṃ negamajānapadā paribhuñjanti, ekaṃ khandhaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"paribhuñjanti, ekaṃ khandhaṃ migā paribhuñjanti."
msgstr ""
"The king and harem made use of one trunk, the troops another, the people of "
"town and country another, ascetics and brahmins another, and beasts and "
"birds another."

#. VAR: na ca sudaṃ → na ca puna (mr)
msgctxt "an6.54:9.8"
msgid ""
"Suppatiṭṭhassa kho pana, brāhmaṇa dhammika, nigrodharājassa na koci phalāni "
"rakkhati, na ca sudaṃ aññamaññassa phalāni hiṃsanti."
msgstr "No-one guarded the fruit, yet no-one damaged another’s fruits."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:10.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, brāhmaṇa dhammika, aññataro puriso suppatiṭṭhassa nigrodharājassa "
"yāvadatthaṃ phalāni bhakkhitvā sākhaṃ bhañjitvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"Then a certain person ate as much as he liked of the fruit, then broke off a "
"branch and left."

# Adhivattha is used virtually exclusively for a deva, and surely deserves a more elevated term than “live”. But we don’t have a positive word for “haunt”.
msgctxt "an6.54:10.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, brāhmaṇa dhammika, suppatiṭṭhe nigrodharāje adhivatthāya devatāya "
"etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then the deity haunting the royal banyan tree thought:"

msgctxt "an6.54:10.3"
msgid "‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho."
msgstr "‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing!"

#. VAR: Yāva pāpo manusso → yāva pāpamanusso (s1-3) | yāvatā pāpamanusso (mr)
msgctxt "an6.54:10.4"
msgid ""
"Yāva pāpo manusso, yatra hi nāma suppatiṭṭhassa nigrodharājassa yāvadatthaṃ "
"phalāni bhakkhitvā sākhaṃ bhañjitvā pakkamissati, yannūna suppatiṭṭho "
"nigrodharājā āyatiṃ phalaṃ na dadeyyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"How wicked this person is, to eat as much as they like, then break off a "
"branch and leave! Why don’t I make sure that the royal banyan tree gives no "
"fruit in future?’"

msgctxt "an6.54:10.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, brāhmaṇa dhammika, suppatiṭṭho nigrodharājā āyatiṃ phalaṃ na adāsi."
msgstr "Then the royal banyan tree gave no more fruit."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.370"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:11.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, brāhmaṇa dhammika, rājā korabyo yena sakko devānamindo "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then King Koravya went up to Sakka, lord of gods, and said to him:"

# The question mark in MS is incorrect. I have corrected it.
msgctxt "an6.54:11.2"
msgid "‘yagghe, mārisa, jāneyyāsi suppatiṭṭho nigrodharājā phalaṃ na detī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Please sir, you should know that the royal banyan tree called Well Planted "
"gives no fruit.’"

# Reading pātesi. This passage is the locus classic for the phrase: “that escalated quickly”.
#. VAR: abhisaṅkhāsi → abhisaṅkhāresi (s1-3, mr)
#. VAR: pavattesi → pātesi (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.54:11.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, brāhmaṇa dhammika, sakko devānamindo tathārūpaṃ iddhābhisaṅkhāraṃ "
"abhisaṅkhāsi, yathā bhusā vātavuṭṭhi āgantvā suppatiṭṭhaṃ nigrodharājaṃ "
"pavattesi ummūlamakāsi."
msgstr ""
"Then Sakka used his psychic powers to will that a violent storm come. And it "
"felled and uprooted the royal banyan tree."

msgctxt "an6.54:11.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, brāhmaṇa dhammika, suppatiṭṭhe nigrodharāje adhivatthā devatā "
"dukkhī dummanā assumukhī rudamānā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr ""
"Then the deity haunting the tree stood to one side, miserable and sad, "
"weeping, with a tearful face."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.371"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:12.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, brāhmaṇa dhammika, sakko devānamindo yena suppatiṭṭhe nigrodharāje "
"adhivatthā devatā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā suppatiṭṭhe nigrodharāje "
"adhivatthaṃ devataṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Sakka went up to that deity, and said:"

msgctxt "an6.54:12.2"
msgid ""
"‘kiṃ nu tvaṃ, devate, dukkhī dummanā assumukhī rudamānā ekamantaṃ ṭhitā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Why, god, are you standing to one side, miserable and sad, weeping, with a "
"tearful face?’"

msgctxt "an6.54:12.3"
msgid ""
"‘Tathā hi pana me, mārisa, bhusā vātavuṭṭhi āgantvā bhavanaṃ pavattesi "
"ummūlamakāsī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Because, my good sir, a violent storm came and felled and uprooted my home.’"

msgctxt "an6.54:12.4"
msgid ""
"‘Api nu tvaṃ, devate, rukkhadhamme ṭhitāya bhusā vātavuṭṭhi āgantvā bhavanaṃ "
"pavattesi ummūlamakāsī’ti?"
msgstr "‘Well, did you stand by your tree’s duty when the storm came?’"

msgctxt "an6.54:12.5"
msgid "‘Kathaṃ pana, mārisa, rukkho rukkhadhamme ṭhito hotī’ti?"
msgstr "‘But my good sir, how does a tree stand by its duty?’"

msgctxt "an6.54:12.6"
msgid ""
"‘Idha, devate, rukkhassa mūlaṃ mūlatthikā haranti, tacaṃ tacatthikā haranti, "
"pattaṃ pattatthikā haranti, pupphaṃ pupphatthikā haranti, phalaṃ phalatthikā "
"haranti."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s when those who need the tree’s roots, bark, leaves, flowers, or fruit "
"take what they need."

#. VAR: anabhinandi → anabhiraddhi (bj)
msgctxt "an6.54:12.7"
msgid "Na ca tena devatāya anattamanatā vā anabhinandi vā karaṇīyā."
msgstr "Yet the deity is not displeased or upset because of this."

msgctxt "an6.54:12.8"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, devate, rukkho rukkhadhamme ṭhito hotī’ti."
msgstr "This is how a tree stands by its duty.’"

msgctxt "an6.54:12.9"
msgid ""
"‘Aṭṭhitāyeva kho me, mārisa, rukkhadhamme bhusā vātavuṭṭhi āgantvā bhavanaṃ "
"pavattesi ummūlamakāsī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I was not standing by a tree’s duty when the storm came and felled and "
"uprooted my home.’"

# Also not a question. I have corrected
msgctxt "an6.54:12.10"
msgid ""
"‘Sace kho tvaṃ, devate, rukkhadhamme tiṭṭheyyāsi, siyā te bhavanaṃ "
"yathāpure’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘God, if you were to stand by a tree’s duty, your home may be as it was "
"before.’"

#. VAR: Ṭhassāmahaṃ → tiṭṭheyyāmahaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "an6.54:12.11"
msgid "‘Ṭhassāmahaṃ, mārisa, rukkhadhamme, hotu me bhavanaṃ yathāpure’ti."
msgstr "‘I will stand by a tree’s duty! May my home be as it was before!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
#. VAR: abhisaṅkhāsi → abhisaṅkhāri (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an6.54:13.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, brāhmaṇa dhammika, sakko devānamindo tathārūpaṃ iddhābhisaṅkhāraṃ "
"abhisaṅkhāsi, yathā bhusā vātavuṭṭhi āgantvā suppatiṭṭhaṃ nigrodharājaṃ "
"ussāpesi, sacchavīni mūlāni ahesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then Sakka used his psychic power to will that a violent storm come. And it "
"raised up that mighty banyan tree and the bark of the roots was healed."

msgctxt "an6.54:13.2"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa dhammika, api nu taṃ samaṇadhamme ṭhitaṃ jātibhūmakā "
"upāsakā pabbājesuṃ sabbaso jātibhūmiyaṃ sattahi āvāsehī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, Brahmin Dhammika, were you standing by an ascetic’s duty "
"when the local lay followers banished you from all seven of the monasteries "
"in your native land?”"

msgctxt "an6.54:13.3"
msgid "“Kathaṃ pana, bhante, samaṇo samaṇadhamme ṭhito hotī”ti?"
msgstr "“But sir, how do I stand by an ascetic’s duty?”"

msgctxt "an6.54:13.4"
msgid ""
"“Idha, brāhmaṇa dhammika, samaṇo akkosantaṃ na paccakkosati, rosantaṃ na "
"paṭirosati, bhaṇḍantaṃ na paṭibhaṇḍati."
msgstr ""
"“When someone abuses, annoys, or argues with an ascetic, the ascetic doesn’t "
"abuse, annoy, or argue back at them."

msgctxt "an6.54:13.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa dhammika, samaṇo samaṇadhamme ṭhito hotī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how an ascetic stands by an ascetic’s duty.”"

msgctxt "an6.54:13.6"
msgid ""
"“Aṭṭhitaṃyeva maṃ, bhante, samaṇadhamme jātibhūmakā upāsakā pabbājesuṃ "
"sabbaso jātibhūmiyaṃ sattahi āvāsehī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I was not standing by an ascetic’s duty when the local lay followers "
"banished me from all seven of the monasteries in my native land.”"

# For AN, BB has changed from “spiritual guide “to” founder of a spiritual sect” for titthakara. But the idiomatic usage seems to be “religious founders”.<a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.54:13.7"
msgid ""
"“Bhūtapubbaṃ, brāhmaṇa dhammika, sunetto nāma satthā ahosi titthakaro kāmesu "
"vītarāgo."
msgstr ""
"“Once upon a time, there was a Teacher called Sunetta. He was a religious "
"founder and was free of sensual desire."

msgctxt "an6.54:13.8"
msgid ""
"Sunettassa kho pana, brāhmaṇa dhammika, satthuno anekāni sāvakasatāni ahesuṃ."
msgstr "He had many hundreds of disciples."

# See BB’s note on this. the text seems corrupt, I give the apparent meaning.
msgctxt "an6.54:13.9"
msgid "Sunetto satthā sāvakānaṃ brahmalokasahabyatāya dhammaṃ desesi."
msgstr "He taught them the path to rebirth in the company of Brahmā."

msgctxt "an6.54:13.10"
msgid ""
"Ye kho pana, brāhmaṇa dhammika, sunettassa satthuno brahmalokasahabyatāya "
"dhammaṃ desentassa cittāni na pasādesuṃ te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ "
"duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Those lacking confidence in Sunetta were—when their body broke up, after "
"death—reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "an6.54:13.11"
msgid ""
"Ye kho pana, brāhmaṇa dhammika, sunettassa satthuno brahmalokasahabyatāya "
"dhammaṃ desentassa cittāni pasādesuṃ te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ "
"saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjiṃsu. (1)"
msgstr ""
"Those full of confidence in Sunetta were—when their body broke up, after "
"death—reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:15.1"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, brāhmaṇa dhammika, mūgapakkho nāma satthā ahosi … pe … (2)"
msgstr "Once upon a time there was a teacher called Mūgapakkha …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:16.1"
msgid "Aranemi nāma satthā ahosi … (3)"
msgstr "Aranemi …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:17.1"
msgid "… Kuddālako nāma satthā ahosi … (4)"
msgstr "Kuddālaka …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:18.1"
msgid "… Hatthipālo nāma satthā ahosi … (5)"
msgstr "Hatthipāla …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.372"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:19.1"
msgid "… Jotipālo nāma satthā ahosi titthakaro kāmesu vītarāgo."
msgstr "Jotipāla. He was a religious founder and was free of sensual desire."

msgctxt "an6.54:19.2"
msgid ""
"Jotipālassa kho pana, brāhmaṇa dhammika, satthuno anekāni sāvakasatāni "
"ahesuṃ."
msgstr "He had many hundreds of disciples."

msgctxt "an6.54:19.3"
msgid "Jotipālo satthā sāvakānaṃ brahmalokasahabyatāya dhammaṃ desesi."
msgstr "He taught them the way to rebirth in the company of Brahmā."

msgctxt "an6.54:19.4"
msgid ""
"Ye kho pana, brāhmaṇa dhammika, jotipālassa satthuno brahmalokasahabyatāya "
"dhammaṃ desentassa cittāni na pasādesuṃ te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ "
"duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Those lacking confidence in Jotipāla were—when their body broke up, after "
"death—reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "an6.54:19.5"
msgid ""
"Ye kho pana, brāhmaṇa dhammika, jotipālassa satthuno brahmalokasahabyatāya "
"dhammaṃ desentassa cittāni pasādesuṃ te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ "
"saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjiṃsu. (6)"
msgstr ""
"Those full of confidence in Jotipāla were—when their body broke up, after "
"death—reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:20.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, brāhmaṇa dhammika, "
msgstr "What do you think, Brahmin Dhammika? "

msgctxt "an6.54:20.2"
msgid ""
"yo ime cha satthāre titthakare kāmesu vītarāge, anekasataparivāre "
"sasāvakasaṃghe paduṭṭhacitto akkoseyya paribhāseyya, bahuṃ so apuññaṃ "
"pasaveyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"If someone with malicious intent were to abuse and insult these six teachers "
"with their hundreds of followers, would they not make much bad karma?”"

msgctxt "an6.54:20.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "an6.54:20.4"
msgid ""
"“Yo kho, brāhmaṇa dhammika, ime cha satthāre titthakare kāmesu vītarāge "
"anekasataparivāre sasāvakasaṃghe paduṭṭhacitto akkoseyya paribhāseyya, bahuṃ "
"so apuññaṃ pasaveyya."
msgstr "“They would indeed."

msgctxt "an6.54:20.5"
msgid ""
"Yo ekaṃ diṭṭhisampannaṃ puggalaṃ paduṭṭhacitto akkosati paribhāsati, ayaṃ "
"tato bahutaraṃ apuññaṃ pasavati."
msgstr ""
"But someone who abuses and insults a single person accomplished in view with "
"malicious intent makes even more bad karma."

msgctxt "an6.54:20.6"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

# See BB’s note on this. It seems to me the sentence is following the previous sections and saying “In non-Buddhist communities, it is not possible to do such harm as it is in the Buddhist community when you harm your spiritual companions”. From BB’s translation, I think he is reading it as saying, “A Buddhist monastic cannot create harm against outsiders in the same way as they do for those in Buddhism.”
#. VAR: evarūpiṃ khantiṃ → evarūpaṃ khantaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "an6.54:20.7"
msgid ""
"Nāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa dhammika, ito bahiddhā evarūpiṃ khantiṃ vadāmi, yathāmaṃ "
"sabrahmacārīsu."
msgstr ""
"Brahmin Dhammika, I say that any injury done by those outside of the "
"Buddhist community does not compare with what is done to one’s own spiritual "
"companions."

msgctxt "an6.54:20.8"
msgid "Tasmātiha, brāhmaṇa dhammika, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So you should train like this:"

# See BB’s note. I accept the most common reading in text and commentaries, “āmasabrahmacarisu”. This follows Edgerton: āmaPage 99, col 2 m., defined in ŚsP as = religious longings (lit. thirsts; could the word be connected with Skt. Lex. āma, m., disease? i.e. pathological state?): ŚsP 486.4–5 …mahāsattvasyāmaḥ; 7 āmaḥ, dharmatr̥ṣṇāḥ; 14–15, 22, etc., dharmatr̥ṣṇā āmaḥ. See s.v. mūdhāma. I think Dhammika was not a monk, but hoping to be one.
#. VAR: na no samasabrahmacārīsu → na no āmasabrahmacārīsu (bj, s1-3) | na no sabrahmacārīsu (si, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.54:20.9"
msgid "‘na no samasabrahmacārīsu cittāni paduṭṭhāni bhavissantī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘We will have no malicious intent for those who we want to have as our "
"spiritual companions.’"

msgctxt "an6.54:20.10"
msgid "Evañhi te, brāhmaṇa dhammika, sikkhitabbanti."
msgstr "That is how you should train."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.373"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:21.1"
msgid "Sunetto mūgapakkho ca,"
msgstr "Sunetta and Mūgapakkha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:21.2"
msgid "aranemi ca brāhmaṇo;"
msgstr "and Aranemi the brahmin,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:21.3"
msgid "Kuddālako ahu satthā,"
msgstr "Hatthipāla the student,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:21.4"
msgid "hatthipālo ca māṇavo."
msgstr "and Kuddālaka were Teachers."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:22.1"
msgid "Jotipālo ca govindo,"
msgstr "And Jotipāla Govinda"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:22.2"
msgid "ahu sattapurohito;"
msgstr "was priest for seven kings."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Ahiṃsakā → ahiṃsete (bj) | abhisekā (s1-3)
msgctxt "an6.54:22.3"
msgid "Ahiṃsakā atītaṃse,"
msgstr "These six famous teachers,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:22.4"
msgid "cha satthāro yasassino."
msgstr "harmless ones of the past,"

# Following text’s adhimutta
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
#. VAR: karuṇedhimuttā → karuṇe vimuttā (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.54:23.1"
msgid "Nirāmagandhā karuṇedhimuttā,"
msgstr "were free of the stench of decay, compassionate,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Kāmasaṃyojanātigā → kāmasaññojanātitā (s1-3)
msgctxt "an6.54:23.2"
msgid "Kāmasaṃyojanātigā;"
msgstr "gone beyond the fetter of sensuality."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:23.3"
msgid "Kāmarāgaṃ virājetvā,"
msgstr "Detached from sensual desire,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: ahuṃ → ahū (si) | ahu (bahūsu)
msgctxt "an6.54:23.4"
msgid "Brahmalokūpagā ahuṃ."
msgstr "they were reborn in the Brahmā realm."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:24.1"
msgid "Ahesuṃ sāvakā tesaṃ,"
msgstr "Many hundreds of"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:24.2"
msgid "Anekāni satānipi;"
msgstr "their disciples were also"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:24.3"
msgid "Nirāmagandhā karuṇedhimuttā,"
msgstr "free of the stench of decay, compassionate,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:24.4"
msgid "Kāmasaṃyojanātigā;"
msgstr "gone beyond the fetter of sensuality."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:24.5"
msgid "Kāmarāgaṃ virājetvā,"
msgstr "Detached from sensual desire,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: ahuṃ → ahū (si) | ahu (bahūsu)
msgctxt "an6.54:24.6"
msgid "Brahmalokūpagā ahuṃ."
msgstr "they were reborn in the Brahmā realm."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:25.1"
msgid "Yete isī bāhirake,"
msgstr "A man who insults"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:25.2"
msgid "vītarāge samāhite;"
msgstr "with hateful intent"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:25.3"
msgid "Paduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo,"
msgstr "these outside hermits,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:25.4"
msgid "yo naro paribhāsati;"
msgstr "free of desire, immersed in samādhi,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:25.5"
msgid "Bahuñca so pasavati,"
msgstr "makes much bad karma."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:25.6"
msgid "apuññaṃ tādiso naro."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:26.1"
msgid "Yo cekaṃ diṭṭhisampannaṃ,"
msgstr "But the man who insults"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:26.2"
msgid "Bhikkhuṃ buddhassa sāvakaṃ;"
msgstr "with hateful intent"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:26.3"
msgid "Paduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo,"
msgstr "a single person accomplished in view,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:26.4"
msgid "Yo naro paribhāsati;"
msgstr "a mendicant disciple of the Buddha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:26.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ tato bahutaraṃ,"
msgstr "makes even more bad karma."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:26.6"
msgid "Apuññaṃ pasave naro."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:27.1"
msgid "Na sādhurūpaṃ āsīde,"
msgstr "You shouldn’t attack a holy person,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:27.2"
msgid "diṭṭhiṭṭhānappahāyinaṃ;"
msgstr "who has given up the grounds for views."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:27.3"
msgid "Sattamo puggalo eso,"
msgstr "This person is called"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:27.4"
msgid "ariyasaṅghassa vuccati."
msgstr "the seventh of the noble Saṅgha."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:28.1"
msgid "Avītarāgo kāmesu,"
msgstr "They’re not free of desire for sensual pleasures,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:28.2"
msgid "yassa pañcindriyā mudū;"
msgstr "and their faculties are still immature:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:28.3"
msgid "Saddhā sati ca vīriyaṃ,"
msgstr "faith, mindfulness, and energy,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:28.4"
msgid "samatho ca vipassanā."
msgstr "serenity and discernment."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:29.1"
msgid "Tādisaṃ bhikkhumāsajja,"
msgstr "If you attack such a mendicant,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:29.2"
msgid "pubbeva upahaññati;"
msgstr "you first hurt yourself."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:29.3"
msgid "Attānaṃ upahantvāna,"
msgstr "Having hurt yourself,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:29.4"
msgid "pacchā aññaṃ vihiṃsati."
msgstr "you harm the other."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:30.1"
msgid "Yo ca rakkhati attānaṃ,"
msgstr "But if you protect yourself,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:30.2"
msgid "rakkhito tassa bāhiro;"
msgstr "the other is also protected."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:30.3"
msgid "Tasmā rakkheyya attānaṃ,"
msgstr "So you should protect yourself."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:30.4"
msgid "akkhato paṇḍito sadā”ti."
msgstr "An astute person is always uninjured.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.54:30.5"
msgid "Dvādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.54:30.6"
msgid "Dhammikavaggo pañcamo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "an6.54:31.1"
msgid "Nāgamigasālā iṇaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:31.2"
msgid "Cundaṃ dve sandiṭṭhikā duve;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:31.3"
msgid "Khemaindriya ānanda,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.54:31.4"
msgid "Khattiyā appamādena dhammikoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "an6.54:31.5"
msgid "Paṭhamo paṇṇāsako samatto."
msgstr ""
